      "content": "i have told doctors. they just give me more pills that don't work or tell me to \"manage\" it. there is no management for this. it’s just constant. i look at people living normal lives and i just feel like a ghost. like i'm already gone, just stuck in this painful skin. it feels more like a mercy to just... not have to be here anymore. to just have some peace and quiet.",
